{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2016}} {{Use Australian English|date=October 2016}} {{Multiple issues| {{notability|Music|date=July 2012}} {{BLP sources|date=July 2012}} }} '''Gerry Joe Weise''' (born 1959) is an Australian guitarist, singer and songwriter, from [[Sydney|Sydney Australia]], who has performed and released music albums in Australia, Europe and the United States of America.<ref>[http://www.gerryjoeweise.com/blues-music.html/ Gerry Joe Weise, Blues music, official website]</ref> He is also a visual artist, known for his installations in [[Land Art]], [[Earth Art]] and [[Environmental art]].<ref>[http://www.gerryjoeweise.com/land-art.html/ Gerry Joe Weise, Land Art, official website]</ref>
He has released solo albums on the Blues Breaking Records label: ''Live and Lost in the Netherlands'' (2018), ''Laon Blues Festival'' (2017), ''Blues Gone Wild'' (2016), ''Stormy Sydney 20th Anniversary'' (2014), ''Live and Proud'' (2012), ''Live Blues World Tour'' (2011), ''Blues Down Under'' (2009), ''Sydney Paris Blues'' (2005), ''Bushman Boogie Deluxe'' (1999), ''Bushman Boogie'' (1998), ''Live in Paris'' (1994); also on the same label are the official singles: ''Blue Concerto for Orchestra (Slide Guitar and Violin)'' (2016), ''Blues for [[Gary Moore]]'' (2011). In 2016 the Australian Blues Rock magazine<ref>[http://www.australianbluesrock.com/ Australian Blues Rock magazine]</ref> had written about the track [[Inside-Looking Out]], from the Blues Gone Wild album: "the [[Eric Burdon]] song performed by Weise's soulful vocals and exciting adventurous guitar playing, intertwining with [[Juma Sultan]]'s congas and percussion; they twine the threads of blues for our future!".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.australianbluesrock.com/|title=Australian Blues Rock magazine|website=Australian Blues Rock magazine|access-date=2016-08-21}}</ref>
Weise's guitar style is [[blues]] fused with [[Rock music|rock]] and [[jazz]]. He has performed at numerous blues and jazz festivals: 1994 Cognac Blues Passions Festival,<ref>[http://2010.bluespassions.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=76&Itemid=197 1994 Cognac Blues Passions Festival]</ref> 1996 30th Commemoration of the first Jimi Hendrix Experience Concert with guest [[Noel Redding]],<ref>[http://www.kathyetchingham.com/evreux-anniversary-plaque-1996/ 1996 30th Commemoration of the first Jimi Hendrix Experience Concert with guest Noel Redding]</ref> 1999 Jazz and Blues Festival Leognan,<ref>[http://www.jazzandblues-leognan.fr/index.cfm?catId=1045 1999 Jazz and Blues Festival Leognan]</ref> 2008 Santa Maria Blues Festival Azores,<ref>[http://www.santamariablues.com/en/portfolio-view/cartaz-2008/ 2008 Santa Maria Blues Festival Azores]</ref> 2009 Grosses Guitares Festival Vaugneray,<ref>[http://www.lesgrossesguitares.com/archives/affiches/#affiche-2009-jpg 2009 Grosses Guitares Festival Vaugneray]</ref> 2009 Scottsdale Art Fest Arizona USA,<ref>[http://www.888artfest.com/art-shows/arizona/artfest-of-scottsdale/scottsdale-entertainment-schedule 2009 Scottsdale Art Fest Arizona USA]</ref> 2010 Blues en VO Festival Paris,<ref>[http://www.bluesenvo.fr/images/progr_bvo_2010.pdf 2010 Blues en VO Festival Paris]</ref> 2012 Presqu'ile Blues Festival Ambialet,<ref>[http://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2012/06/14/1377962-5e-festival-de-blues-a-ambialet.html 2012 Presqu'ile Blues Festival Ambialet]</ref> 2013 Hookrock Festival Diepenbeek Belgium,<ref>[http://www.pbase.com/bluesadventure/image/148725172 2013 Hookrock Festival Diepenbeek Belgium]</ref> 2013 Unhate Festival Paris with band member [[Juma Sultan]],<ref>[http://www.billetreduc.com/search.htm?se=gerry+joe+weise%2C+juma+sultan&type=3 2013 Unhate Festival Paris with band member Juma Sultan]</ref> 2014 Gardenstock Festival Dixon Illinois USA with band member [[Juma Sultan]],<ref>[https://issuu.com/shawmedia/docs/gaz_08182014 2014 Gardenstock Festival Dixon Illinois USA with band member Juma Sultan]</ref> 2014 Blues on Broadbeach Festival Australia,<ref>[http://www.weekendnotes.com/blues-on-broadbeach-music-festival/ 2014 Blues on Broadbeach Festival Australia]</ref> 2017 and 2018 Mitchell Creek Rock 'N' Blues Fest Australia,<ref>[https://www.mitchellcreekrocknbluesfest.com.au/schedule/?Dayid=2/ 2017 Mitchell Creek Rock 'N' Blues Fest Australia]</ref><ref>[https://www.mitchellcreekrocknbluesfest.com.au/schedule/?Dayid=5/ 2018 Mitchell Creek Rock 'N' Blues Fest Australia]</ref> 2018 Goodna Jacaranda Festival Australia.<ref>[https://goodnajacarandafestival.com/program/ 2018 Goodna Jacaranda Festival Australia]</ref>
Weise has released books both in paperback and ebooks: ''Earth Art'' (2017), ''Land Art'' (2018). Ludovic Gibsson wrote the introduction for Earth Art: “Earth Art, 70th Exhibition Celebration. This book is a celebration of the 70 exhibitions Weise has produced from 1982 to 2017, spanning 35 years in the international art world. It is a gateway to the understanding of the more difficult avenues of his art, through his own thoughts, analysis and influences. A witness to his style of Earth Art, which encompasses elements of Land Art, Installation Art, Environmental Art, Ephemeral Art and “In Situ”. The several layers of meaning that often bewildered critics, who were unable to fathom his application of the Alter-modern, his diaspora, while using physics and philosophy".<ref>[http://www.gerryjoeweise.com/earth-art-book.html/ Gerry Joe Weise, Earth Art book, official website]</ref>
